<div class="info-body">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
        <div class="mr-auto col-2"> <a class="btn btn-primary back" href="/" role="button">Back</a></div>
        <div class="ml-auto col-10"><h1><b>Full Serve 3D-Printing</b> </h1></div>
    </div>

    <div class="d-flex justify-content-md-between">
        <div class="mr-auto col-6 faq">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <p>
                <b>Q:Who is eligable?</b><br>
                A: Full-Serve printing is available to anyone with a &#x00040 ucalgary.ca email and associated UCID#.<br />

                <b>Q: What type of machine/printing material do we use?</b><br>
                A: At the TFDL makerspace we have a Prusa MK3S 3D-Printer. We use  a thermoplastic polymer made strictly
                from renewable resources called PLA filament. This material is BPA free.<br>

                <b>Q: What is the cost to print?</b><br>
                A: $2.00 set up fee + $ 0.30 per gram.<br>

                <b>Q: Acceptable sizing for job submissions?</b><br>
                A: The maximum dimensions for singular object designs are 200 x 200 x 180 mm. Weight limit is 180g.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mr-auto col-6 confirm">
            <h2>Submit A Print Job</h2>
            <p>
                Once you have confirmed that your model is of acceptable sizing and weight, please ensure that your model
                is also <b>watertight</b>, more information available at <a href="https://transmagic.com/six-reasons-watertight-models-matter/">https://transmagic.com/six-reasons-watertight-models-matter/</a>.
                After the above steps are completed, save your model as a .stl file and submit it below. Please contact us if
                you are experiencing any errors with the online form or have questions not answered here.
            </p>
            <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary form" onclick="location.href = '/fullserveform';">Online Form</button>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="policies">
        <h2>Printing Policies</h2>
        <p>
            1. TFDL 3D printers may only be used for academic purposes. Usage for commercial purposes is strictly prohibited.<br>
            2. TFDL reserves the right to refuse any 3D printing request.<br>
            3. TFDL is not responsible for model stability and quality. Please ensure that your model is watertight and
            structurally sound prior to submission.<br>
            4. All models must be picked up within 30 days of completion. All models left for more than 30 days become property
            of the library.
        </p>
    </div>

</div>

